title: MCU OC (Metahuman 1)
body:
Full Name: Janice Katherine Loren-Wyndward

AKA: Cascade (codename), Jayn Loren (preferred)

Hero or Villain: Hero, formerly antihero

Looks: here // 5'3.5" // 135 lbs // 28 yrs old (Infinity War) // hero outfit

Vices: impulsive, vengeful, lacks social skills common for her age

Virtues: resourceful, humorous, brave, encouraging 

Biography: Jayn was raised by her mother for 5 years, until some agents stormed their house. She was hidden in a closet for her protection, and listened as they took her mom away. Nearly a day later, someone came and took her to live with her father, a rich man who owned and managed a brilliant R&D company. She discovered her powers at the age of 10, and quickly began to master her capabilities, on her own. Soon after, she took her inheritance (which she was made to receive once she graduated) and traveled the world, learning self-defense, projectile throwing, and espionage tactics. Then she went to go find her mom, who apparently had been taken for developing a biochemical weapon serum—the one that had given Jayn her powers in utero through exposure to it. Destroying multiple weapon organizations with her skills, she eventually focused on SHIELD.

Power(s): Hydrokinesis/genesis (of all states of water), which she uses for attacks, defense, and accelerated cellular regeneration (though it only goes about 1.5x faster than the regular human rate, so she still can die from severe trauma). She often controls bursts of water vapor to create warmth or help herself glide through the air. Jayn has a scientific understanding of her powers, which gives her great control over her abilities, but she loses this control if she gets too emotional.

Weapon(s): Mostly just her powers. Occasionally she’ll use things from her utility belt that she wears on missions (EMP device, lockpicks, and/or her trusty backup knife) but those are more emergency tools than anything else.

Skills: swimming, parkour, knife throwing, martial arts, willpower/built up resistance to cold

Fears: She’s mostly afraid of being alone/unloved and not being good enough. She dislikes dark tiny spaces and feeling like she’s being controlled. She hates thunder.

Sexuality: Pansexual

Family: Dahlia Loren (mother, deceased); Robert Wyndward (father, alive/estranged); Meranda “Mila” Lauren Wong (biological daughter, alive)

Extras:
-she has ADHD
-her daughter is an Avenger like her
-has killed exactly 52 people; she tries not to kill though

(FC is Meagan Tandy)

summary: 'Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse' Sequel to Focus on Miles Morales and Gwen Stacy Romance
title: 'Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse' Sequel to Focus on Miles Morales and Gwen Stacy Romance
excerpt: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse is now swinging into theaters, but it's already been enough of [...]
description:
“…one of Pascal’s favorites, Gwen Stacy, will lead the way. The producer revealed that Sony’s upcoming Into the Spider-Verse sequel… will be focused on Miles Morales and Gwen Stacy—and will explore a romance between the two, a thread from Lord’s original script that ultimately didn’t fit in Into the Spider-Verse.”

Speaking as someone who haven’t yet seen the movie and has to base his opinion on the source material and how it has handled this “romance”:

summary: So I used to babysit this kid, and his mom works with Chris Evans’s mom at a health club or something and she got the kid a...
body:
So I used to babysit this kid, and his mom works with Chris Evans’s mom at a health club or something and she got the kid a signed Captain America poster because why not, right?


No.


This kids has never seen a Marvel movie, never wants to see a Marvel movie, and has no interest whatsoever in having anything that Chris Evans has touched.


WYD.
